SIMPLE: regulator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regulator
<hw>Reg"u*la`tor</hw> <pr>(-l?`t?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, regulates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A contrivance for regulating and
controlling motion</def>, <specif>as:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
lever or index in a watch, which controls the effective length of the
hairspring, and thus regulates the vibrations of the balance.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The governor of a steam engine.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>A valve for controlling the admission of steam to the steam chest,
in a locomotive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A clock, or other timepiece, used as a standard of
correct time. See <cref>Astronomical clock</cref> <sd>(a)</sd>, under
<er>Clock</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A member of a volunteer committee which, in default
of the lawful authority, undertakes to preserve order and prevent
crimes; also, sometimes, one of a band organized for the comission of
violent crimes.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A few stood neutral, or declared in favor of the
<qex>Regulators</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reguline</ent>⟦br⟧
